Week 8: Relativity and Black Holes
======
- Lorentz Factor:  $$\gamma = \frac {1} {\sqrt{1-\frac{v^2}{c^2}}} \ge 1$$
- Lorentz Transformations:
$$ x' = \frac {x-vt} {\sqrt{1-\frac{v^2}{c^2}}} = \gamma (x-vt)$$, 
$$ t' = \frac {t- \frac {vx} {c^2}} {\sqrt {1- \frac {v^2} {c^2}}} = \gamma (t-\frac {vx} {c^2})$$
- Invariant Interval: 
$$ s^2 = c^2t'^2 - x'^2 = c^2t^2-x^2 $$
- Momentum Invariant: 
$$ P = \frac {mv} {\sqrt{1- \frac{v^2}{c^2}}} = \gamma mv$$
- Energy Invariant: 
$$ E = \frac {mc^2} {\sqrt{1- \frac {v^2}{c^2}}} = \gamma mc^2$$
- Length Contraction
$$ L' = L \sqrt{ 1- \frac {v^2}{c^2}} = \frac{L }{\gamma}$$
- Time Dilation
$$ T' = \frac {T} {\sqrt{1- \frac {v^2}{c^2}}} = \gamma T$$

